    "description": "The 3e-030-2 Security Server Cryptographic Core (Version 3.0) provides FIPS 140-2 validated cryptographic functionality for the 3eTI Security Server product, a RADIUS-like back-end Authentication Server, capable of dynamic key exchange, support of JITC DoD-signed certificates for PKI usage, and full 802.11i support. The 3e-030-2 provides the following FIPS-approved cryptographic algorithms: AES (ECB mode; 256-bit key size), SHA-1, HMAC-SHA1, RSA sign/verify, FIPS 186-2 (Appendix 3.1 and 3.2 3.3) PRNG. The 3e-030-2 also supports the following non-FIPS cryptographic algorithms: Diffie Hellman",
